reviewText:
Take one dash Xcom:EU;
Add a western setting with thematic gear choices and abilities like ricochet shots and fanning;
An adventure overmap setting with a choose-your-own-adventure style choice and consequences system;
Introduce some neat combat game mechanics like positioning of the sun/characters causing shadows that gives you away, interactable environments to create cover such as kicking tables over etc;
Get the Witcher 3's music composer to create some nice atmosphere along with the great VA of the Narrator;
Customize your playstyle and character builds even further with the playing card stat/ability system (And even make proper poker hands for extra bonuses!);
And finally add a dash of the supernatural and satanic elements to give it that Shadows of Brimstone inspired charm;
And the result you get is Hard West, a charming affordable little tactical TBS with an interesting story and another entry into the success and viability of the Kickstarter funding system.
